misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes that their implementation correctly performs a single right shift on the array, utilizing a temporary variable to save the wrapped element and a loop to displace all other elements sequentially. The code structure shows a textbook approach to solving this specific array manipulation problem.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: There is no conceptual gap related to the Java execution model. The student accurately applies linear time complexity (O(N)) sequential memory manipulation (array indexing, assignment, loops) to achieve the desired transformation. The approach of saving the last element, shifting elements from right-to-left (to avoid overwriting unshifted data), and finally inserting the saved element at the front is standard and correct.
